('More', 'UK', 'More is the first full-length soundtrack album, and third studio album, by the English rock band Pink Floyd, released on 13 June 1969 in the United Kingdom by EMI Columbia and on 9 August 1969 by Tower Records a subsidiary label of Capitol Records in the United States as Original Motion Picture Soundtrack from the film More.', 4.06, 'https://img.discogs.com/YF7rneGUVTGM8kVo_xBhpa_2qS0=/fit-in/600x590/filters:strip_icc():format(jpeg):mode_rgb():quality(90)/discogs-images/R-1240780-1475092749-5675.jpeg.jpg', '1969-06-13', 'Rock', 'Psychedelic');
